<br>
1. Jboots or Sow is essential<br>
2. Fluxstaff is real real real handy<br>
<br>
Zonein from DL, head left along the wall till you see the hornet nest. Find a nice spot to med.<br>
<br>
Mobinfo:<br>
A scoriae hornet approx hp 5000 warriorclassed <br>
A ash hornet approx hp 1500 warriorclassed<br>
A ember hornet approx hp 3500 warriorclassed<br>
A cinder hornet approx hp 2500 warriorclassed<br>
<br>
Ash hornets are all green at 51 so not a good target. Seems a pretty good target for lower level quadders with CoF. Plenty of them to go around. 9/10 dont give exp for a lvl 51 though.<br>
<br>
Scoriae hornets highblue at 51 and have a ton of HP. Not advisable to quad these regularly. They resist quite a bit and they are not really common. These drop spells from time to time.<br>
<br>
Cinder hornets are highgreen to lowblue at 51 and ALL of them give exp. Prime target for a quadkite. Semicommon spawns, low hp.<br>
<br>
Ember hornets are all blue at 51. Also a prime target for 51. Semicommon spawns also.<br>
<br>
Loot includes gems, cash upto 7pp and some crappy stuff<br>
<br>
These things are slow as hell and easily outrun with jbooties. resist MR: medium resist Cold: low resist Fire: High.<br>
<br>
Okies, onto to the pullingbit<br>
<br>
Hornet nest has three static spawns and they spawn very regulary (faster then you can quad/med). Move just in range of them and flux all three. If you can't flux em all three just run down the hill, come back up and get the rest. Now find a wanderer to complete the quad.<br>
<br>
Note: sometimes you will have to clear out a few ash hornets because they are part of the 3 static spawns. Also scoriae will spawn as one of the 3 statics once in a while. Just take him in your quad and slo him up after the rest is done. Possibly have to medkite him if you take him in your quad. Cinders and emebers are the most common of the 3 static spawn possibilities.<br>
<br>
Move a bit to DLzone, there's a clearing before you hit all the trees. Go to external view, circle around till you get em together. Now back to 1st person, straight line, run run run. Use your flux staff to determine distance. Out of range stop. Cast atols spectral shackles. snared all four hopefully, run, cast lvl 51 pillar of frost etc etc etc. Finish off and cleanup.<br>
<br>
Note: If you get stunned while doing this because of a to short circle your chances of survival are slim.<br>
<br>
If you get one resist on snare either root mob down and snare it. Wait till root breaks, bunch up and snare again.<br>
<br>
Or the easy way, Circle around the snared mobs till snaretime is up and resnare. Fullproof but takes 2 minutes longer.<br>
<br>
If you get two resist use above method.<br>
<br>
I had at least one resist every 1 of 4 quads so be prepared to handle it.<br>
<br>
Manausage and exp:<br>
<br>
Lvl 51 203 int +mana 265 specialize evocation<br>
4 Cinder hornets leaves you with just under 50 mana if all goes well (pretty good for four expkills)<br>
4 Ember hornets leaves you with just over 30mana if all goes well.<br>
<br>
2 quads ussually leaves you with 1 blue bub depending on what was in those two quads.<br>
<br>
All in all a great place to practice quadkiting and way better exp. The three static spawns really help out on the time needed to gather a quad. Maybe a bit more time then one solo kill but its not much of a difference. Medtime is minimal since you will have harvest up. So from 50 to at least 60 mana with harvest, med 40 up and GTG.<br>
<br>
One more note: Theres room for only 1 lvl 51 quadding here since you really need the three statics for you quad or it will take forever to find 4 roamers. All below 51 can quad the ash hornets i think, There are loads of those around.<br>
<br>
This was my second day of quadkiting so dont blame for not being an expert at it (yet, hehehehe)<br>
